==English==
===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|ȝarly}}, {{m|enm|ȝarely}}, from {{inh|en|ang|ġearlīċe}}, {{m|ang|ġearolīċe}}; equivalent to {{suffix|en|yare|ly}}.
===Adverb===
{{en-adv}}
# {{lb|en|archaic}} In a [[yare]] way.
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Antony and Cleopatra|II|ii|text={{...}}The silken tackle / Swell with the touches of those flower-soft hands / That '''yarely''' frame the office.}}
#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Tempest|I|i|text={{...}}Fall to't '''yarely''', or we run ourselves aground. Bestir, [[bestir]]!}}
